      • TlsClientHelloMessage

        public TlsClientHelloMessage(TlsVersion clientVersion,
                             TlsRandom clientRandom,
                             TlsSessionId sessionId,
                             java.util.List<TlsCipherSuite> cipherSuites,
                             java.util.List<TlsExtension> extensionList)
        Creates a client hello message.
        Parameters:
        clientVersion - the highest TLS version the client supports
        clientRandom - the client chosen random value
        sessionId - the session ID. Should be empty for new connections and can contain a session ID of an old connection to resume.
        cipherSuites - a list of supported cipher suites sorted by preference
        extensionList - a list of extensions, which should be used for this connection
